Number = {4},
Pages = {484-488},
Abstract = {Dalechampia brownsbergensis sp. nov. from Surinam belongs to sect.
   Scandentes. It differs from other members of the section in bearing only
   small, vestigial resiniferous bractlets and in being pollinated by male
   euglossine bees. It also differs from the common and somewhat similar
   species D. tiliifolia by having involucral bracts that are green at
