Year = {2004},
Volume = {199},
Number = {4},
Pages = {273-285},
Abstract = {All the steps leading to anther opening, pollen presentation, and
   dispersal are reviewed and discussed. The main aspects are anther
   dehydration and its mechanisms, pollen dehydration and how pollen is
   presented and leaves the anther. Mechanisms of anther opening vary among
   plants; when anthers open pollen may be actively expelled, staying in
   the anther until dispersal. Modes of pollen presentation and dispersal
   aspects are examined in the light of: type of pollen dispersal unit;
   water content of pollen; type of carbohydrate reserves; conversion of
   carbohydrates from insoluble to soluble and vice versa to adjust turgor
   for environmental conditions and any mechanisms to avoid water loss
   during exposure and dispersal.},
